            <title>[CASSANDRA-10768] Optimize the way we check if a token is repaired in anticompaction</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10768</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we anticompact we check each token if it is within a repaired range, this is very inefficient with many tokens as we do a linear search instead of sorting the ranges and doing a binary search (or even just keeping track of the next right-boundary and checking against that to avoid 2 comparisons)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
